%erg v1
Title: Route .erg ticket mutations through erg binary instead of direct file edits
Status: open
Created: 2026-04-29
Author: claude

--- log ---
2026-04-29T14:00Z claude created

--- body ---
## Context

`beat.py` and orchestrator sessions currently mutate `.erg` ticket files
via direct `Edit`/`Write`/`Bash` tool calls. This hits the Claude Code
permission layer, which has been observed to deny these operations even
under `--permission-mode bypassPermissions` (see ticket 0052).

The root fix is to route all `.erg` mutations through the `erg` Go binary
(e.g., `erg close <id>`, `erg log <id> <entry>`), which runs as a plain
subprocess and bypasses the Claude permission model entirely. The erg-side
commands are being designed on the git-erg repo.

This ticket tracks the IDH-side adoption once the erg binary exposes the
necessary commands.

## Blocked-by

The erg binary must expose ticket-mutation commands (close, log, status-set)
before this ticket can be implemented. Track progress on the git-erg repo;
unblock this ticket when those commands land.

## Actions

1. Audit every place in `beat.py` and `skills/` that directly writes or
   edits a `.erg` file. Produce a list.

2. For each mutation site, replace the direct file edit with the
   corresponding `erg` CLI call (e.g., `subprocess.run(["erg", "close",
   ticket_id], ...)` or via a helper wrapper).

3. Remove the belt-and-suspenders allow-list entries in `beat-settings.json`
   added by ticket 0052, if they were only needed as a workaround.

4. Update `test_beat.py` to mock `subprocess.run(["erg", ...])` calls
   rather than file-write operations.

## Exit criteria

- No `.erg` file is written by Claude tool calls (`Edit`, `Write`, `Bash`
  with redirection) anywhere in `beat.py` or `skills/`; all mutations go
  through `erg` subprocesses.
- Beat runs on `.claude` project show zero `denied:Edit` / `denied:Write`
  entries in beat-log (no permission friction at all, not just bypassed).
- `test_beat.py` covers the erg-subprocess path for ticket close and log.
